As a noun, it means any action, stratagem, or other means of concealing or preventing investigation or exposure. For example, "The company was involved in a cover-up of its financial scandals."- **Pun Meaning**: When "Cover-Up" is combined with "Class" to form "Cover-Up Class", it becomes a pun on "Proletariat". The term "Proletariat" refers to the class of workers who own no property and work for wages. Here, "Cover-Up Class" is used humorously or critically to refer to a group of people who try to cover up or suppress information, instead of the original meaning of the working class.
